      "ot_chromium_trial_name": "DeclarativeCSSModules",
      "ot_description": "Declarative CSS Modules Scripts are an extension of the existing script-based CSS Module Scripts. They allow for developers to share declarative stylesheets with shadow roots, including declarative shadow roots. Developers can define inline style modules with <style type=\"module\" specifier=\"foo\"> and apply a declarative module to a declarative shadow DOM by referencing specifier or a URL, such as <template shadowrootmode=\"open\" shadowrootadoptedstylesheets=\"foo\">.",
