  "motivation": "Without this feature, developers have several non-ideal options for sharing a set of styles between declarative shadow DOM hosts:\n\n1. Use imperative CSS Modules, somewhat defeating the purpose of declarative shadow DOM, because it requires script and must happen after the declarative shadow DOM has been parsed.\n2. Duplicating <style> tags, resulting in more work for parser and more work for the developer to update dynamically.\n3. Use external CSS files in a <link> tag, resulting in a potential Flash of Unstyled Content (FOUC), as well as more work for the developer to update dynamically.",
